quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  38,27,"And We did not create the heavens and the earth and what is between them in vain. That is the thinking of those who disbelieve. So, woe to the disbelievers because of the Fire (they have to face)."
  38,28,"Shall We make those who believe and do righteous deeds equal to those who commit mischief on the earth? Or shall We make the God-fearing equal to the sinners?"
  38,29,"This is a blessed Book We have revealed to you, so that they deliberate in its verses and, and so that the men of understanding may take to advice."
  38,30,"And We blessed Dawud with Sulayman. He was an excellent slave (of Allah). Surely, he was great in turning (to Us, in penitence and praise)."
  38,31,"(Worth remembering is the incident) when the swift horses of high breeding were presented before him in the evening."
  38,32,"He said, “ I held the love of the good things (i.e. these horses) dearer than the remembrance of my Lord, until it (the sun ) went behind the veil."
  38,33,"Bring them back to me" - and he started passing his hands over the shanks and the necks."
  38,34,"And We, indeed, tested Sulayman while We threw on his throne a body after which he turned (to Us)."
  38,35,"He said, "0 my Lord, forgive me, and bless me with a kingdom that will not be available to anyone after me. Surely, You are the Bountiful."
  38,36,"Then We subjugated the wind for him that blew smoothly on his command to wherever he wished,"
  38,37,"and (We subjugated to him) the shaitans (among Jinns), all builders and divers,"
  38,38,"and many others held in chains."
  38,39,"This is Our gift. So, do favor (to someone) or withhold (it), with no (requirement to give) account."
  38,40,"He has a place of nearness in Our presence, and an excellent end."
  38,41,"And remember Our slave, Ayyub (Job) - when he called his Lord, "The Shaitan (Satan) has inflicted weariness and pain upon me.""
  38,42,"(Allah said to him,) "Strike (the ground) with your foot: Here is a cool water to bathe, and a drink!""